Dear Starbucks Singapore, why did my Strawberry Cheesecake Frappuccino look like that, and tasted worst? I had to throw it away, it was undrinkable.

When I questioned your staff on why doesn't it have any cheesecake taste, like those in Japan, a staff replied saying "You can go to Malaysia or Thailand, and it will taste different also. It may have the same name but it will taste different all over the world." He added that "no ingredient in this recipe has any cheesecake flavouring, except for the whipped cream which is cheese flavoured. It's just in the name." 

I don't think this is professional, but I am not pleased with the look and taste of the drink I purchased from StarbucksSG, and how this case was handled when I brought it to the attention of your staff.
